name: Corral Andino
description:
When walking through the mountains in northwestern Argentina, it is common to see animal pens made of rocks in what seems to be the middle of nowhere, but they are part of a deeply rooted network of communities inhabiting these areas from millennia.


Date: 	September 2021
Location: Huaira Huasi, 23°34'25"S 65°14'07"W
Resolution: 3217px x 5356px
